= page_title "Loop a video"

:textile
  Looping a video is possible using our "JavaScript API":/javascript-api.

  The following is a simple example of the code needed to achieve this:

  h4. HTML Code

:coderay
  #{coderay_options(:html)}
  <video class="sublime" poster="posterframe.jpg" width="640" height="360" preload="none">
    <source src="video.mp4" />
    <source src="video.webm" />
  </video>

:textile
  **Notes**

  This is the normal code discussed in the "Quickstart Guide":/quickstart-guide.

  h4. JavaScript Code

  Put this code in a @<script>@ element just before the @</body>@ tag, or in an external file.

:coderay
  #{coderay_options(:javascript)}
  sublimevideo.ready(function() {
    sublimevideo.onEnd(function(sv) {
      sublimevideo.play(sv.element);
    });
  });

:textile
  **Notes**

  If you donâ€™t want to loop all of the videos in your page, you can add conditions before calling "(c)@sublimevideo.play@":/javascript-api/methods#play (for example adding an @id@ to your @<video>@ element and then perform a check on @sv.element.id@).

  h3. Demo

  You can see this feature in action "on this page":http://test.sublimevideo.net/loop.
